<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 30 at 2:40PM CDT  by NWS Birmingham</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern
Marengo, southwestern Perry, southwestern Hale and southwestern
Dallas Counties through 315 PM CDT...
At 239 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Faunsdale, or near Uniontown, moving south at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Uniontown, Thomaston, Newbern, Faunsdale, Dayton, Bogue Chitto,
Consul, Central Mills, Arcola, Marion Junction, Perry County
Correctional Center, Gallion, Safford, Vaiden Field Airport and
Laneville.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
